    "citation": "Yukawa 2006 16789993",
    "population": "N: 74 (Japanese) Age: 50.5±13.4 WT: 59.0±11.0 [CYP2C19] *1/*1: 33 *1/*2: 31 *1/*3: 4 *2/*2: 3 *2/*3: 3",
    "model_type": "PK",
    "objective": "“to clarify using population pharmacokinetic analysis whether CYP2C19 polymorphism affects the pharmacokinetics of phenytoin and phenobarbital in patients with normal CYP2C9”",
    "covariates": "Tested: - Included: WT, PHT concentration, CYP2C19 on CL",
    "observations": "The data used for this study was exactly the same as the 2000 Mamiya study. It is unclear why they re-analysed the data, except for the quantification of PHT effect on PHB CL. At a typical PHT concentration of 15 mg/L, PHB CL was found to be reduced by 23.4%. Other parameters were close to those reported by Mamiya et al.",
    "dose": "Steady-state oral doses in patients",
    "structure": "Simplified PK",
    "equations": "G1=0 if(CYP2C19==11 | CYP2C19==22 | CYP2C19==23†) G1=1 CL/F=theta1*((WT/60)**theta2)*(PHTc**theta3)*(1+theta4**G1)*(1+eta1) Css=D/(CL*Tau) Cobs=Css*(1+eps1) PHTc: measured PHT concentration † if CYP2C19 is one of *1/*1, *2/*2 or *2/*3, the individual is a poor metabolizer Theta1 was reported as mL/kg/day, but given that this would lead to very high concentrations with normal doses, it was assumed that it should have said mL/kg/h, this was then converted to L/h. Theta2 was converted due to CL conversion",
    "parameter_values": "theta1=0.3174 theta2=0.280 theta3=-0.0985 theta4=0.807 omega1=0.049 sigma1=0.020",
    "validation": "No / No"
  },
